<detall><id label=""><![CDATA[78143]]></id><title label="Titol"><![CDATA[Roni Horn's work is at the Fundació Joan Miró]]></title><excerpt label="Resum"><![CDATA[The exhibition includes sculptural installations, photographic series, working drawings and a floor piece by the New York artist.]]></excerpt><content label="Contingut"><![CDATA[<p>The exhibition Everything was sleeping as if the universe were a mistake, conceived by the artist herself, explores the various resources she has used over the last 20 years.</p>
<p>It includes the main themes and formats that have shaped her work: sculptural installations, photographic series, working drawings and floor piece. The title, Everything was sleeping as if the universe were a mistake, is taken from the Livro do desassossego by Fernando Pessoa.</p>
